        <h3 data-uuid="a12939a6ef3d46c99594851bafd43f57">Amendments</h3>
        <p data-uuid="ee893ae324314f3ab14971fc65cc7cd8">The framers of the Constitution also included a method for changing or adding to the Constitution. They wanted the government to be able to adapt as changes were needed. The process for amending, or adding <dfn title="amendment">amendments</dfn> to, the Constitution was made difficult. A major change to the government would require the approval of two-thirds of each house of Congress and three-fourths of states before it could take effect.</p>
